CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1952, pg. 1 reads: "Happy Moments in Lives Of These "Favorite Churchwomen" - These five contestants shared honors last Thursday night in A. Leo Weil School Auditorium. Left: the Rev. Jefferson Henderson is pictured accepting the check for $25 presented him by Mrs. Anna Gentry..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Rev. Jefferson Henderson holding check with Anna Gentry, with P.L .Prattis, seated on left, and Jessie Vann, standing on right, gathered on stage in A. Leo Weil school during "Favorite Churchwoman's" contest award program
